<article>
	<header class="Manchet">
		<h1>Colors<small> — styleguide</small></h1>
	</header>

	<div class="Container">
		<p>Links are <a href="#">red</a> — unless inside a navigation bar or tabs where they can be either white or black.</p>
		<p>Red is also used to highlight selected items.</p>

		<h2>All colors</h2>
		<p>Here's a list of all colors from config.scss - it's not dynamic though so it might be out of date.</p>
	</div>
	<div class="Container Container--full">
		<style>
			.Colors {
				display: flex;
				flex-flow: row wrap;
			}
			.Colors-item {
				flex: 0 1 10rem;
				padding: 1rem 1rem 0.9rem;
				text-transform: capitalize;
			}
		</style>
		<figure class="Colors">
			{{#each model.colors as |color|}}
				<div class="Colors-item" style="background-color: {{{color.value}}};">
					{{color.title}}
				</div>
			{{/each}}
		</figure>
		<figure class="Colors">
			{{#each model.grays as |color|}}
				<div class="Colors-item" style="background-color: {{{color.value}}};">
					{{color.title}}
				</div>
			{{/each}}
		</figure>
	</div>
</article>
